<Layout title="PrimeFlux — The Mathematics of Distinction">
  <section class="container mx-auto py-16 px-4">
    <h1 class="text-5xl font-garamond mb-8 text-center">PrimeFlux</h1>
    <p class="text-xl mb-8 text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      The mathematics of distinction and reversible reality.
    </p>
    <div class="text-center mb-8">
      <a href="/PrimeFlux_Isaacson_2025.pdf" class="bg-prime-gold text-prime-blue px-8 py-4 rounded-lg font-bold text-xl hover:bg-opacity-80 inline-block">
        Download the 403-Page Thesis (PDF)
      </a>
    </div>
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <p class="text-lg mb-4">
        PrimeFlux is a number-theoretic framework in which:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-lg mb-8">
        <li>Primes are irreducible distinctions on dual rails (6k±1).</li>
        <li>Composites are structured superpositions.</li>
        <li>Flux conservation (∇·Φ = 0) is the fundamental axiom.</li>
        <li>Balance occurs at Re(s) = 1/2, resolving all seven Clay Millennium Problems as corollaries.</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-center text-xl italic mb-4">
        From these axioms alone, mathematics becomes reversible — and intelligence becomes ethical.
      </p>
      <div class="text-center">
        <a href="/ethics" class="text-prime-gold hover:underline">See how it powers our ethics</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
